PowOS Window Zones — Default Layouts
=====================================

This directory ships PowOS's default KZones layouts. KZones is a KWin script
that brings FancyZones-style window snapping to KDE Plasma.

See also: `powos zones list` (shows all layouts with zone coordinates)
          `powos zones edit` (opens the config for customization)


Bundled Layouts
---------------

1. Halves                          — Left 50% | Right 50%
2. Thirds                          — Left 33% | Center 34% | Right 33%
3. Priority Center                 — Side 25% | Center 50% | Side 25%
4. Priority Left                   — Main 67% | Stack 33%
5. Ultrawide: 3-Col Balanced       — Side 25% | Center 50% | Side 25%
6. Ultrawide: Big Center + Side Stacks — Center 50% + 4 stacked side zones

Column detents used: ¼ (25%), ⅓ (33%), ½ (50%), ⅔ (67%), ¾ (75%)

The "Ultrawide" layouts are identical in proportions to their 16:9 counterparts
but are named separately so you can tell the active layout from the KZones OSD.


Activation UX
-------------

Zones appear automatically when you begin dragging any window.
Drop the window onto a highlighted zone — it snaps to fill that zone.

Shortcuts:
  Ctrl+Alt+C           Toggle zone overlay on/off manually
  Ctrl+Alt+0-9         Snap the active window to zone N directly
  Meta+Arrow keys      Move window between zones directionally
  Ctrl+Alt+D           Cycle through layouts

Note: right-click during drag is NOT supported on Wayland. The KWin scripting
API does not expose pointer-button events during compositor-managed interactive
moves. Auto-show on drag is used instead (identical feel, no modifier needed).


Customising Layouts
-------------------

Layouts are JSON: an array of layout objects, each with a "name", "padding"
(pixels), and "zones" (array of {x, y, width, height} in screen-percent).

Option A — system-wide (affects all users; requires sudo or a rebuilt image):
  Edit /etc/xdg/kwinrc, section [Script-kzones], key layoutsJson.
  Paste the JSON array as a single line. After saving:
    qdbus org.kde.KWin /KWin reconfigure

Option B — per-user (overrides A):
  Open System Settings → Window Management → KWin Scripts → KZones → Configure
  Paste your layout JSON in the "Layouts" field.

Option C — CLI helper:
  powos zones edit     (opens System Settings KZones config page, or kwinrc)

Zone coordinate system:
  (0,0) is top-left of the screen.
  x, y, width, height are all percentages of the screen dimensions.

Example — left-third + right-two-thirds:
  {"name": "My Layout", "padding": 4, "zones": [
    {"x": 0,  "y": 0, "width": 33, "height": 100},
    {"x": 33, "y": 0, "width": 67, "height": 100}
  ]}
